40:12.108 --> 40:13.977
<i>Dear Marcus,</i>

40:14.010 --> 40:15.579
<i>I can't see you.</i>

40:15.612 --> 40:18.182
<i>You'll only run away
from me again,</i>

40:18.215 --> 40:20.517
<i>this time when you see
the scar</i>

40:20.550 --> 40:22.986
<i>across the width
of my wrist.</i>

40:23.018 --> 40:24.954
<i>Had you seen it
the night of our date,</i>

40:24.987 --> 40:27.523
<i>I would have
honestly explained it to you.</i>

40:27.556 --> 40:30.126
<i>I was prepared to do that.</i>

40:30.159 --> 40:31.928
<i>I didn't try to cover it up,</i>

40:31.961 --> 40:34.097
<i>but as it happened,
you failed to notice it.</i>

40:35.898 --> 40:37.768
<i>It's a scar from a razor.</i>

40:37.800 --> 40:40.703
<i>I tried to kill myself.</i>

40:40.737 --> 40:44.141
<i>That's why I went
for three months to the clinic.</i>

40:44.173 --> 40:48.077
<i>It was the Menninger Clinic
in Topeka, Kansas...</i>

40:48.110 --> 40:51.080
<i>the Menninger Sanitarium
and Psychopathic Hospital.</i>

40:51.114 --> 40:54.083
<i>There's the full name
for you.</i>

40:54.117 --> 40:58.522
<i>My father the doctor
knows people there.</i>

40:58.554 --> 41:01.257
<i>I used the razor
when I was drunk.</i>

41:01.291 --> 41:04.260
<i>If I had been sober,
I would have succeeded.</i>

41:04.293 --> 41:06.730
<i>So three cheers
for 10 rye and gingers.</i>

41:06.762 --> 41:08.865
<i>They're why I'm alive today.</i>

41:11.300 --> 41:14.170
<i>That and my incapacity
to carry anything out.</i>

41:15.271 --> 41:17.842
<i>Even suicide is beyond me.</i>

41:20.844 --> 41:23.146
<i>I don't regret
doing what we did,</i>

41:23.179 --> 41:25.648
<i>but we mustn't
do anything more.</i>

41:26.916 --> 41:28.284
<i>Forget about me, Marcus.</i>

41:28.318 --> 41:30.653
<i>There's no one
around here like you.</i>

41:30.686 --> 41:32.522
<i>You're not a simple soul</i>

41:32.556 --> 41:34.625
<i>and have no business
being here.</i>

41:34.657 --> 41:37.728
<i>If you survive
the squareness of this place,</i>

41:37.760 --> 41:39.896
<i>you'll have a sterling future.</i>

41:39.929 --> 41:43.900
<i>Why did you come to Winesburg
to begin with?</i>

41:43.934 --> 41:46.169
<i>I came because it's so square.</i>

41:46.202 --> 41:49.039
<i>That's supposed to make me
a normal girl.</i>

41:49.072 --> 41:51.041
<i>But you...</i>

41:51.074 --> 41:53.644
<i>you should be studying
philosophy at the Sorbonne</i>

41:53.677 --> 41:56.179
<i>and living in a garret
in Montparnasse.</i>

41:56.211 --> 41:58.981
<i>We both should.</i>

41:59.014 --> 42:01.984
<i>Farewell, beauticious man.</i>

42:02.018 --> 42:03.554
<i>Olivia.</i>

42:27.277 --> 42:29.278
<i>Olivia!</i>

42:29.311 --> 42:33.083
<i>You forgot
your allowance.</i>

42:33.115 --> 42:34.818
We'll see you
at Thanksgiving.

42:34.851 --> 42:36.686
Your mother
will join us.

43:02.778 --> 43:05.114
Ah. What employment
have we here?

43:05.148 --> 43:07.818
Please, no Shakespeare
rehearsal tonight.

43:13.155 --> 43:14.157
Hey!

43:14.190 --> 43:15.726
By my life,

43:15.759 --> 43:17.394
this is my lady's hand.

43:17.427 --> 43:20.364
These be her very "C"s,
her "U"s, and her "T"s.

43:20.396 --> 43:22.732
Thus makes she her...

43:24.400 --> 43:27.169
To the unknown beloved,
this, and my good wishes:

43:27.202 --> 43:28.338
her very phrases!

43:28.371 --> 43:30.039
By your leave, wax.

43:30.072 --> 43:31.974
Soft! and the impressure
her very Lucrece,

43:32.007 --> 43:34.210
with which she uses
to seal: 'tis my lady.

43:34.244 --> 43:35.746
<i>To whom should this be?</i>

43:35.778 --> 43:37.748
<i>Jove knows I love:
But who?</i>

43:37.780 --> 43:40.317
Lips, do not move;
No man must know.

43:40.349 --> 43:41.817
God damn it, Flusser!

43:41.851 --> 43:43.320
No man must know.

43:43.353 --> 43:45.155
What follows?
The numbers altered.

43:45.188 --> 43:46.289
No man must know:

43:46.322 --> 43:48.826
unless this should
be thee, Malvolio?

43:50.126 --> 43:51.394
What the...

43:51.427 --> 43:52.996
what the hell
is wrong with you?!

43:53.028 --> 43:54.398
Hey, stop getting
all worked up.

43:54.431 --> 43:56.032
How about a little bit
of respect, huh?

43:56.065 --> 43:57.800
What?

43:57.833 --> 44:00.302
What? That's from
the one that blew you?

44:00.335 --> 44:01.904
In my car?

44:01.938 --> 44:04.173
How about
respecting my car

44:04.206 --> 44:06.710
by not driving around
with some slut in it.

44:30.467 --> 44:32.035
You are in luck.

44:32.068 --> 44:34.004
There is a vacancy
in Neil Hall.

44:34.036 --> 44:36.706
Mrs. Burgess in Housing
can get you the key.

44:36.739 --> 44:39.008
It's rather rustic.

44:39.041 --> 44:42.813
Oh, and you will need to schedule
a chat with Dean Caudwell.

44:42.846 --> 44:45.347
He likes to be informed
of these kinds of changes.

44:45.380 --> 44:49.251
Can you come by Monday,
say, 2:30?

44:49.284 --> 44:50.319
Sure.

45:07.170 --> 45:12.142
Volunteers are still needed
for homecoming weekend.

45:12.175 --> 45:15.077
As you know,
last year's defeat

45:15.110 --> 45:18.013
<i>at the hands
of College of Wooster</i>

45:18.047 --> 45:20.817
<i>broke a winning streak
that will require,</i>

45:20.849 --> 45:23.819
<i>I shall say,
all hands on deck,</i>

45:23.853 --> 45:26.523
<i>which we will redress,
hence the need.</i>

45:26.556 --> 45:29.259
<i>I speak on behalf
of Coach Blauvelt</i>

45:29.291 --> 45:31.494
<i>when I say the Bulldog bite</i>

45:31.527 --> 45:36.265
<i>can only be commensurate
with a Bulldog bark.</i>

45:36.298 --> 45:38.434
<i>We are, all of us,</i>

45:38.467 --> 45:41.070
<i>responsible
to the Bulldog bark.</i>

46:09.164 --> 46:10.367
Olivia.

46:10.400 --> 46:11.535
Olivia, please.

46:11.568 --> 46:13.170
Yes, Marcus?

46:15.003 --> 46:17.239
If...

46:17.273 --> 46:19.976
if you could just...

46:20.009 --> 46:22.978
sit next to me
again in class,

46:23.012 --> 46:25.916
it would really
help me concentrate.

46:25.949 --> 46:28.385
It's harder when
you're behind me.

46:28.418 --> 46:30.019
I keep wanting
to turn around.

46:32.621 --> 46:34.457
Okay, maybe.

46:36.592 --> 46:39.461
All right.
Thank you.

46:39.494 --> 46:41.565
I heard you moved rooms.

46:44.032 --> 46:46.068
Yeah. I...

46:46.101 --> 46:50.840
I had a disagreement
with my roommates.

46:50.873 --> 46:52.275
I moved
to Neil Hall.

46:54.409 --> 46:56.879
You weren't
in Chapel yesterday.

46:56.913 --> 46:59.282
Honestly,
I just needed a break.

46:59.315 --> 47:01.851
I don't know how much more
of Dr. Donehower's

47:01.885 --> 47:04.855
going on about
"Christ's example" I can take.

47:04.887 --> 47:06.922
Maybe you could get
some kind of waiver

47:06.956 --> 47:09.059
for conscientious
objection.

47:09.092 --> 47:10.427
Why's that?
Because I'm Jewish?

47:10.460 --> 47:11.561
I don't object
because I'm Jewish.

47:11.594 --> 47:12.896
I object because
I'm an atheist.

47:12.929 --> 47:14.431
I know.

47:19.034 --> 47:20.569
Thank you
for talking to me.

47:20.603 --> 47:22.405
If I talk to you again,

47:22.438 --> 47:25.175
maybe you won't have to
stand under my window all the time.

47:27.577 --> 47:30.046
Oh.

47:30.079 --> 47:32.015
Um...

47:32.047 --> 47:33.449
I, uh...

47:34.617 --> 47:36.186
You know, it's funny.

47:36.219 --> 47:39.489
I don't actually know
which window is yours.

47:39.521 --> 47:42.291
I'm on the third floor,
on the left,

47:42.324 --> 47:45.027
facing the quad,
just for the record.

47:45.061 --> 47:47.297
I rarely see you
looking up.

47:47.329 --> 47:50.067
If you're not a Peeping Tom,
what's the point?

47:51.199 --> 47:53.603
Guess it just
makes me feel as if...

47:56.472 --> 48:01.044
like I'm making sure
you're okay.

48:01.077 --> 48:03.480
Oh, Marcus, I'm fine.

48:05.014 --> 48:07.384
It's you
I'm worried about.

48:10.652 --> 48:12.321
You can come in now.

48:20.496 --> 48:21.999
Come on in.

48:32.641 --> 48:34.644
Marcus Messner.

48:37.146 --> 48:39.449
I wanted you to come in
so we could meet

48:39.481 --> 48:41.617
and find out if I could
be of any help to you

48:41.650 --> 48:43.585
in adjusting
to Winesburg.

48:43.619 --> 48:45.221
I see by your transcript

48:45.253 --> 48:48.223
that you're a remarkably
gifted student.

48:48.257 --> 48:51.494
First in your family
ever to attend college.

48:51.527 --> 48:55.030
Captain of your baseball team
at high school.

48:55.063 --> 48:57.232
Scholarship
from your temple.

48:57.266 --> 48:59.536
I wouldn't want
anything at Winesburg

48:59.568 --> 49:01.271
to interfere
in the slightest

49:01.304 --> 49:03.373
with such a stellar record
of achievement.

49:03.405 --> 49:05.007
Neither do I, sir.

49:09.478 --> 49:14.016
Do you see any potential difficulties
on the horizon here?

49:14.050 --> 49:16.119
No, sir.
I don't, sir.

49:16.152 --> 49:18.121
How are things going
with your class work?

49:18.153 --> 49:20.389
You're getting all you hoped for
from your courses?

49:20.422 --> 49:22.257
Yes. Yes, sir.

49:22.291 --> 49:23.727
You're socializing
enough?

49:23.760 --> 49:26.296
Yes.

49:26.329 --> 49:29.065
Yes, I am, sir.

49:35.338 --> 49:36.740
Thank you, sir.

49:39.442 --> 49:41.411
The only problem
is that you seem to have

49:41.443 --> 49:44.413
some trouble settling
into dormitory life.

49:44.447 --> 49:46.548
Tell me,
in your own words,

49:46.581 --> 49:48.217
what seems to be
the trouble?

49:50.385 --> 49:52.554
I'm sorry, could you
repeat your question, sir?

49:52.588 --> 49:54.157
Calm down, son.

49:54.190 --> 49:55.592
Try a little more water.

49:58.594 --> 50:02.432
And no need to call me sir,
by the way.

50:02.465 --> 50:03.667
So...

50:05.300 --> 50:07.536
what was the problem
with your accommodations?

50:07.570 --> 50:10.539
In the room to which
I was assigned,

50:10.572 --> 50:13.542
one of my...
roommates

50:13.576 --> 50:16.311
would always play the phonograph
after I went to bed,

50:16.344 --> 50:18.748
and I was not able to get
a good night's sleep.

50:20.215 --> 50:22.317
I need my sleep
in order to do my work.

50:22.351 --> 50:25.121
The situation was...

50:25.153 --> 50:26.623
insupportable.

50:26.655 --> 50:28.590
But couldn't you sit down
and work out a time

50:28.623 --> 50:30.192
for his playing
the phonograph

50:30.226 --> 50:32.429
that was agreeable
to the two of you?

50:32.461 --> 50:35.431
You had to move out?
There was no other choice?

50:35.465 --> 50:37.700
I had to move out.

50:37.733 --> 50:40.070
No way of reaching
a compromise?

50:40.103 --> 50:43.072
Did you seek the support
of your other roommate?

50:43.106 --> 50:45.642
There was no compromise
with him, sir,

50:45.675 --> 50:47.677
and my other roommate
was not sympathetic.

50:47.710 --> 50:50.646
Are you often unable
to reach a compromise

50:50.679 --> 50:52.614
with people whom you
don't see eye to eye with?

50:52.648 --> 50:54.416
I wouldn't say often, sir.

50:54.449 --> 50:56.318
I wouldn't say anything like this
has happened before.

50:56.351 --> 50:57.619
Really, Marcus,

50:57.652 --> 50:59.755
you don't have to do that,
calling me "sir".

50:59.789 --> 51:01.357
Call me Dean Caudwell,

51:01.389 --> 51:03.092
or call me Dean,
if you like.

51:03.126 --> 51:05.461
Winesburg isn't
a military academy.

51:05.494 --> 51:08.498
I don't mind
calling you sir, Dean.

51:08.530 --> 51:12.268
It says here that your father
is a kosher butcher.

51:12.300 --> 51:14.670
No. No, it does not.

51:14.704 --> 51:17.673
I remember
just writing down just "butcher."

51:17.706 --> 51:19.775
That's what
I would write down on any form.

51:19.809 --> 51:21.878
Well, that's what
you did write.

51:21.911 --> 51:25.648
I'm merely assuming
that he's a kosher butcher.

51:25.681 --> 51:28.518
He is, but that is
not what I wrote down.

51:28.550 --> 51:30.686
I acknowledged that.

51:30.719 --> 51:33.388
But it's not inaccurate,
is it,

51:33.422 --> 51:37.159
to identify him more precisely
as a kosher butcher?

51:37.193 --> 51:40.130
Neither is what I wrote down
inaccurate, sir.

51:40.163 --> 51:43.666
I'd be curious to know why you
didn't write down "kosher," Marcus.

51:45.268 --> 51:47.871
Sir, if you are
asking me if I was trying to hide

51:47.903 --> 51:49.606
the religion into
which I was born,

51:49.639 --> 51:51.208
the answer is no.

51:52.440 --> 51:54.409
Well, I certainly
hope that's so.

51:54.443 --> 51:56.846
I'm glad to hear that.

51:56.878 --> 52:00.849
Everyone has a right
to openly practice his own faith,

52:00.882 --> 52:02.818
and that holds true
at Winesburg

52:02.851 --> 52:05.754
just as it does
everywhere else in this country.

52:05.788 --> 52:09.458
On the other hand, under
"religious preference,"

52:09.492 --> 52:11.327
I see you
didn't write "Jewish,"

52:11.360 --> 52:13.596
though you are
of Jewish extraction.

52:13.628 --> 52:15.464
And, in accordance
with the college's attempt

52:15.498 --> 52:18.601
to assist students in residing
with others of the same faith,

52:18.634 --> 52:22.204
you were assigned
Jewish roommates.

52:22.237 --> 52:25.207
I didn't write anything
under religious preference, sir.

52:25.240 --> 52:26.775
I can see that.

52:26.809 --> 52:28.511
I'm wondering why that is.

52:28.543 --> 52:31.513
It's because
I have none.

52:31.547 --> 52:35.518
I don't prefer to practice
one religion over another.

52:35.550 --> 52:39.454
What then, provides you
with spiritual sustenance?

52:39.487 --> 52:42.457
To whom do you pray
when you need solace?

52:42.490 --> 52:44.427
I don't need
solace, sir.

52:44.460 --> 52:47.329
I don't believe in God.

52:47.362 --> 52:49.298
I don't believe
in prayer.

52:49.331 --> 52:51.233
I am sustained
by what is real.

52:51.266 --> 52:53.869
Praying, to me,
is preposterous.

52:53.902 --> 52:55.471
Is it, now?

52:55.503 --> 52:57.507
And yet
so many millions do it.

52:57.539 --> 53:00.643
Millions once thought
the Earth was flat, sir.

53:01.911 --> 53:04.246
Yes, that's true.
But may I ask you, Marcus,

53:04.280 --> 53:05.615
merely out of curiosity,

53:05.648 --> 53:08.617
how do you
get by in life,

53:08.650 --> 53:12.621
filled as life is inevitably
with trials and tribulations,

53:12.655 --> 53:14.490
lacking
spiritual guidance?

53:14.523 --> 53:15.892
I get
straight "A"s, sir.

53:15.925 --> 53:19.229
I didn't ask
about your grades.

53:19.262 --> 53:21.364
I know your grades.

53:21.396 --> 53:22.965
You have every right
to be proud of them,

53:22.998 --> 53:24.399
as I've already told you.

53:24.432 --> 53:25.701
Well, then you
know the answer

53:25.735 --> 53:28.238
to your question
of how I get by, just fine.

53:28.271 --> 53:30.242
Well, if I may say so,
it doesn't look

53:30.243 --> 53:32.243
to me like you get along just fine.

53:32.275 --> 53:34.644
Seems to me as soon as there's
a difference of opinion,

53:34.677 --> 53:36.512
you pick up and leave.

53:36.545 --> 53:39.581
Is there a problem with finding
a solution in quietly leaving?

53:39.614 --> 53:41.283
But look where
you've wound up.

53:41.317 --> 53:45.255
In the least desirable room
on the entire campus.

53:45.288 --> 53:47.456
Frankly, I don't
like the idea of you up there alone.

53:47.489 --> 53:48.757
But I did
not end up there

53:48.791 --> 53:51.594
because of lack
of religious beliefs, sir,

53:51.626 --> 53:55.398
if that's what you are suggesting
in a roundabout way.

53:55.431 --> 53:56.833
Why is it, then?

53:58.467 --> 54:00.403
As I explained
to you before,

54:00.436 --> 54:01.804
the living arrangements
I was given

54:01.836 --> 54:03.306
were intolerable.

54:03.338 --> 54:05.275
Tolerance appears
to be something

54:05.307 --> 54:06.909
of a problem for you,
young man.

54:06.942 --> 54:09.679
I've never heard that
said about me before, sir.

54:09.711 --> 54:11.280
There appear
to be several things

54:11.313 --> 54:13.048
you've never heard
about yourself before.

54:13.081 --> 54:15.585
But before,
you were living at home

54:15.617 --> 54:18.587
in the bosom
of your childhood family.

54:18.621 --> 54:22.291
Now you are living
at Winesburg as an adult,

54:22.324 --> 54:24.760
and aside from mastering
your studies,

54:24.793 --> 54:27.596
your task is to learn
how to get along with people

54:27.630 --> 54:30.300
and to extend tolerance
to those

54:30.333 --> 54:32.535
who may not be
carbon copies of yourself.

54:32.568 --> 54:33.936
Tolerance.

54:33.969 --> 54:37.639
How about extending
some tolerance to me, sir?

54:37.672 --> 54:41.076
Look, I, I don't
mean to be brash or insolent,

54:41.110 --> 54:44.681
but what exactly is the crime
I have committed?

54:44.713 --> 54:46.516
Here? Today?

54:46.548 --> 54:48.016
So I've
switched rooms.

54:48.050 --> 54:50.687
Is that considered a crime
here at Winesburg?

54:50.719 --> 54:53.088
Has anyone
said it is a crime?

54:53.121 --> 54:56.925
You display a fondness
for dramatic exaggeration.

54:56.958 --> 54:58.994
It doesn't serve you well

54:59.027 --> 55:01.997
and is a characteristic
you might want to reflect upon.

55:02.030 --> 55:05.367
Now tell me, how do you
get along with your family?

55:05.400 --> 55:08.904
I see from the form here
you also have no siblings,

55:08.938 --> 55:11.340
so it's just you and
your parents at home,

55:11.373 --> 55:13.742
if I'm to take what you've
written here to be accurate.

55:13.775 --> 55:16.346
Why wouldn't it
be accurate?

55:16.378 --> 55:18.847
I was accurate when
I wrote down my father is a butcher.

55:18.880 --> 55:20.549
He is a butcher.

55:20.583 --> 55:23.052
It isn't I alone
who would describe him as a butcher.

55:23.085 --> 55:25.954
He would describe
himself as a butcher.

55:25.987 --> 55:28.623
You described him
as a kosher butcher,

55:28.657 --> 55:30.992
which is fine, but that is
not grounds for intimating

55:31.025 --> 55:33.495
that I've been in any way inaccurate
in filling out my application...

55:33.528 --> 55:34.864
If I may interrupt,
Marcus,

55:34.896 --> 55:37.866
how do you three get along,
from your perspective?

55:37.900 --> 55:39.635
That's the question
I asked.

55:39.668 --> 55:41.037
You, your mother
and your father,

55:41.070 --> 55:42.638
how do you get along?

55:42.670 --> 55:44.440
A straight answer,
please.

55:50.079 --> 55:52.081
My mother and I get along
perfectly well.

55:52.114 --> 55:54.083
We always have.

55:54.115 --> 55:56.853
So have my father and I
for most of my life.

56:00.822 --> 56:02.991
From my last year
at grade school

56:03.025 --> 56:06.528
until I moved
to Winesburg,

56:06.561 --> 56:09.431
I worked part time
for him at the shop.

56:09.465 --> 56:13.570
We were as close
as father and son could be.

56:15.737 --> 56:18.573
Of late, there's been
some strain between us.

56:18.606 --> 56:21.076
Strain over what,
may I ask?

56:21.110 --> 56:22.678
He's been...

56:22.710 --> 56:26.114
unnecessarily worried
about my independence.

56:26.148 --> 56:30.119
I think it has to do
with many of my cousins

56:30.152 --> 56:32.021
having died
in the last war.

56:32.054 --> 56:34.757
You say unnecessarily
worried about you,

56:34.789 --> 56:36.558
because he has
no reason to be?

56:36.592 --> 56:38.126
None at all.

56:38.159 --> 56:39.728
Is he worried,
for instance,

56:39.762 --> 56:41.831
about your inability
to adjust

56:41.864 --> 56:44.500
to your roommates
here at Winesburg?

56:44.532 --> 56:47.502
I have not told him
about my roommates.

56:47.536 --> 56:49.505
I did not think
it was important.

56:49.538 --> 56:52.007
Nor is
"inability to adjust"

56:52.041 --> 56:55.010
a proper way to describe
the difficulty, sir.

56:55.043 --> 56:57.446
I do not want
to be distracted

56:57.480 --> 57:00.016
from my studies
by superfluous problems.

57:00.048 --> 57:02.451
I wouldn't consider your having
to move out of your room

57:02.485 --> 57:03.952
a superfluous problem,

57:03.985 --> 57:06.121
and neither would
your father, I'm sure,

57:06.155 --> 57:08.224
if he were apprised
of the situation,

57:08.257 --> 57:11.159
as he has every right
to be, by the way.

57:11.193 --> 57:14.030
But be that as it may,

57:14.063 --> 57:17.967
have you gone on any dates
since you've been to Winesburg?

57:18.000 --> 57:19.668
Dates?

57:19.702 --> 57:21.504
Dates.

57:22.704 --> 57:24.473
Yes.

57:24.507 --> 57:25.675
Yes, I have.

57:25.708 --> 57:26.843
A few?

57:26.876 --> 57:29.144
Some? Many?

57:29.177 --> 57:31.114
One.

57:32.213 --> 57:34.183
Just one?

57:35.818 --> 57:38.187
Sir, I object to being
interrogated like this!

57:38.219 --> 57:40.155
I do not see
the purpose of it.

57:40.188 --> 57:41.857
These are my own
private affairs,

57:41.891 --> 57:43.526
as is my religious life,

57:43.559 --> 57:45.894
my social life,
and how I conduct it.

57:45.927 --> 57:47.762
I have broken no laws,

57:47.795 --> 57:49.931
I have caused no one
injury or harm,

57:49.965 --> 57:51.767
and in no way
have my actions

57:51.800 --> 57:54.135
impinged
on anyone's rights.

57:54.168 --> 57:57.138
<i>If anyone's rights
have been impinged on, they are mine.</i>

57:57.172 --> 57:59.509
Sit down, please,
and explain yourself.

57:59.541 --> 58:03.144
I also object to having to attend
Chapel 40 times

58:03.177 --> 58:05.047
before I graduate
in order to earn a degree.

58:05.079 --> 58:07.516
I do not see where the college
has the right

58:07.550 --> 58:09.818
to force me to listen
to a clergyman,

58:09.851 --> 58:12.788
of whatever faith,
even once.

58:12.820 --> 58:14.757
Or listen
to a Christian hymn

58:14.789 --> 58:16.726
invoking
the Christian deity,

58:16.759 --> 58:19.295
given that I am
an atheist who is, to be truthful,

58:19.327 --> 58:23.099
<i>deeply offended by the practices
of organized religion.</i>

58:23.132 --> 58:26.302
I am altogether capable of leading
a moral existence

58:26.335 --> 58:28.103
without
crediting beliefs

58:28.137 --> 58:31.007
that are impossible
to substantiate and beyond credulity.

58:31.039 --> 58:34.876
I take it you are
familiar, Dean Caudwell,

58:34.909 --> 58:37.547
with the writings
of Bertrand Russell.

58:37.579 --> 58:39.614
Bertrand Russell,

58:39.648 --> 58:42.285
<i>the distinguished
mathematician and philosopher</i>

58:42.318 --> 58:43.719
<i>who was last year's
recipient</i>

58:43.751 --> 58:45.755
<i>of the Nobel Prize
in Literature.</i>

58:45.788 --> 58:48.958
The work of literature in which
he was awarded the Nobel Prize

58:48.990 --> 58:51.960
is his widely read essay,
"Why I Am Not a Christian."

58:51.994 --> 58:54.130
Are you familiar
with this essay, sir?

58:54.163 --> 58:55.798
Marcus, please sit down.

58:55.831 --> 58:57.700
<i>Sir, I was asking you
if you are familiar</i>

58:57.733 --> 58:59.635
<i>with this very important essay
by Bertrand Russell,</i>

58:59.668 --> 59:01.570
and I take it
the answer is no.

59:01.603 --> 59:04.573
Well, I am very familiar
with this essay,

59:04.606 --> 59:07.242
because I set myself
the task of memorizing

59:07.275 --> 59:09.277
large sections of it

59:09.311 --> 59:12.280
when I was captain
of my high school debating team.

59:12.313 --> 59:15.317
Now, if you were
to read this essay...

59:15.351 --> 59:18.287
and in the interest
of open-mindedness,

59:18.320 --> 59:20.823
I would urge you
to do so...

59:20.856 --> 59:23.125
you would see
that Bertrand Russell

59:23.157 --> 59:26.127
undoes with logic
that is beyond dispute

59:26.161 --> 59:27.963
the first-cause
argument,

59:27.996 --> 59:29.297
the natural-law
argument,

59:29.331 --> 59:31.000
the argument
from design,

59:31.032 --> 59:32.801
the moral arguments
for a deity,

59:32.835 --> 59:35.804
and the argument
for the remedying of injustice.

59:35.838 --> 59:38.807
Having studied
these arguments,

59:38.840 --> 59:41.242
I intend to live my life
in accordance with them,

59:41.275 --> 59:43.778
as I am sure you would
have to admit, sir,

59:43.811 --> 59:45.213
I have
every right to do.

59:45.246 --> 59:46.949
Please sit down.

59:52.920 --> 59:54.590
I'm sorry.

01:00:03.065 --> 01:00:06.034
I see here that you are
studying to be a lawyer.

01:00:06.068 --> 01:00:08.738
On the basis
of this interview,

01:00:08.771 --> 01:00:12.642
I think you are destined
to be an outstanding lawyer.

01:00:12.675 --> 01:00:15.277
I can see you
one day arguing a case

01:00:15.309 --> 01:00:18.847
before the Supreme Court
and winning it.

01:00:18.880 --> 01:00:22.917
I admire your directness,
your diction,

01:00:22.951 --> 01:00:25.887
your sentence structure,

01:00:25.920 --> 01:00:28.890
even if I don't necessarily
choose to admire

01:00:28.923 --> 01:00:31.427
whom or what
you choose to read

01:00:31.460 --> 01:00:35.197
and the gullibility
with which you take at face value

01:00:35.230 --> 01:00:39.101
rationalist blasphemies
spouted by an immoralist

01:00:39.134 --> 01:00:41.170
of the ilk
of Bertrand Russell,

01:00:41.202 --> 01:00:44.105
four times married,
a blatant adulterer,

01:00:44.139 --> 01:00:47.876
an advocate of free love,
a self-confessed socialist

01:00:47.909 --> 01:00:50.346
dismissed from
his university position

01:00:50.378 --> 01:00:53.214
and imprisoned during
the First War by the British

01:00:53.248 --> 01:00:55.184
for what in plain English
I would call treason.

01:00:55.217 --> 01:00:56.786
What about
the Nobel Prize?!

01:00:56.818 --> 01:00:58.186
I even admire you
now, Marcus,

01:00:58.219 --> 01:01:01.289
when you hammer on my desk
and point to me

01:01:01.322 --> 01:01:03.725
so as to ask
about the Nobel Prize.

01:01:03.759 --> 01:01:05.461
You have
a fighting spirit.

01:01:05.494 --> 01:01:07.329
I'm sorry, sir. I didn't know
that I pointed.

01:01:07.362 --> 01:01:08.864
I didn't mean
to point.

01:01:08.896 --> 01:01:11.099
You did, son.
Not for the first time

01:01:11.132 --> 01:01:13.335
and probably
not for the last.

01:01:13.367 --> 01:01:14.969
But that is
the least of it.

01:01:15.003 --> 01:01:18.974
To find that Bertrand Russell
is a hero of yours

01:01:19.007 --> 01:01:21.342
comes as no great surprise.

01:01:21.376 --> 01:01:23.312
There are
always one or two

01:01:23.344 --> 01:01:26.815
intellectually precocious students
on every campus,

01:01:26.849 --> 01:01:30.152
self-appointed members
of an elite intelligentsia

01:01:30.184 --> 01:01:31.953
who need
to elevate themselves

01:01:31.987 --> 01:01:34.356
and feel superior
to their fellow students,

01:01:34.389 --> 01:01:37.358
superior even
to their professors.

01:01:37.391 --> 01:01:42.097
Nonetheless, that is not what we
are here to discuss.

01:01:42.130 --> 01:01:44.866
What worries me,
rather,

01:01:44.900 --> 01:01:47.168
is your isolation.

01:01:47.202 --> 01:01:50.272
What worries me is
your outspoken rejection

01:01:50.304 --> 01:01:53.509
of long-standing
Winesburg tradition,

01:01:53.541 --> 01:01:57.512
as witness your response
to Chapel attendance,

01:01:57.545 --> 01:01:59.781
a simple undergraduate
requirement

01:01:59.815 --> 01:02:01.383
which amounts to,
on average,

01:02:01.416 --> 01:02:04.353
little more than a few minutes
per week of your years here.

01:02:04.385 --> 01:02:07.355
In all my experience
at Winesburg,

01:02:07.389 --> 01:02:09.892
I have never
come across a student

01:02:09.925 --> 01:02:11.460
who objected
to that requirement

01:02:11.492 --> 01:02:14.462
as an infringement
on his rights.

01:02:14.496 --> 01:02:18.233
What worries me
is how poorly

01:02:18.266 --> 01:02:22.137
you are fitting in to
the Winesburg community.

01:02:22.170 --> 01:02:26.141
To me, it seems something to be
attended to promptly

01:02:26.175 --> 01:02:28.544
and nipped in the bud.

01:02:28.577 --> 01:02:31.313
I, I can't take
any more of this.

01:02:31.346 --> 01:02:33.282
Sir, I think
I'm going to vomit.

01:02:33.315 --> 01:02:34.817
Excuse me?

01:02:34.849 --> 01:02:36.518
I feel ill.

01:02:36.552 --> 01:02:39.521
I think
I'm going to vomit.

01:02:39.554 --> 01:02:42.524
I cannot bear being
lectured like this.

01:02:42.557 --> 01:02:44.326
I'm not a malcontent.

01:02:44.358 --> 01:02:46.961
I am not a rebel.

01:02:46.994 --> 01:02:49.964
I have the right
to socialize

01:02:49.998 --> 01:02:52.534
or not socialize
with whomever I see fit.

01:02:52.568 --> 01:02:55.538
Furthermore, your argument
against Bertrand Russell

01:02:55.570 --> 01:03:00.543
is not an argument against his ideas
based on reason,

01:03:00.576 --> 01:03:03.545
but an argument
against his character,

01:03:03.579 --> 01:03:07.349
i.e., an ad hominem attack,

01:03:07.382 --> 01:03:09.818
which is
logically worthless.

01:03:09.851 --> 01:03:11.886
Sir, I respectfully ask
your permission

01:03:11.920 --> 01:03:13.322
to stand up and leave now,

01:03:13.355 --> 01:03:14.456
because
I am afraid if I don't,

01:03:14.489 --> 01:03:16.125
I am going to be sick.

01:03:16.157 --> 01:03:17.960
Of course you may leave.

01:03:17.992 --> 01:03:20.962
I just ask that you
reflect on why leaving

01:03:20.996 --> 01:03:22.364
appears to be
the only way

01:03:22.396 --> 01:03:24.933
you are dealing
with your problems here.

01:03:24.967 --> 01:03:28.938
I'm genuinely sorry if you think
I've been wasting your time.

01:03:28.971 --> 01:03:32.507
Leaving is not how I cope
with my difficulties.

01:03:32.541 --> 01:03:36.144
I strongly object to you
saying that, Dean Caudwell.

01:03:36.177 --> 01:03:39.013
Well, at least
we got over calling me "sir".

01:03:39.047 --> 01:03:41.150
Marcus,
just one last thing.

01:03:41.182 --> 01:03:43.451
I have the impression
from your application

01:03:43.485 --> 01:03:46.021
that you're
a talented baseball player.

01:03:46.054 --> 01:03:49.557
Would you give a thought about
going up for the Winesburg team?

01:03:49.590 --> 01:03:53.261
I played for that team myself
when I was a student here.

01:03:53.295 --> 01:03:54.563
Dean Caudwell,
my high school

01:03:54.596 --> 01:03:56.231
had the worst team
in the league.

01:03:56.264 --> 01:03:58.199
I don't think
I could play at this level.

01:03:58.233 --> 01:04:00.402
The pitching would be a lot faster
than what I'm used to,

01:04:00.434 --> 01:04:02.003
and I don't think...

01:04:02.036 --> 01:04:04.138
choking up on the bat
the way I did at home

01:04:04.172 --> 01:04:05.541
is going to solve
my hitting problems

01:04:05.574 --> 01:04:07.543
at this level
of competition.

01:04:07.576 --> 01:04:10.179
So you're saying you're
not going out for baseball

01:04:10.211 --> 01:04:11.579
because of the competition?

01:04:11.612 --> 01:04:14.115
No, I am saying
that I am realistic

01:04:14.148 --> 01:04:16.451
about my chances
for making the te...

01:04:21.322 --> 01:04:23.058
<i>Alice!</i>

01:04:35.603 --> 01:04:37.906
<i>I was always a light sleeper,</i>

01:04:37.940 --> 01:04:39.909
<i>though I could
never remember my dreams</i>

01:04:39.942 --> 01:04:42.543
<i>or even whether
I had any dreams.</i>

01:04:42.577 --> 01:04:45.281
<i>But for that day,
and night and day,</i>

01:04:45.313 --> 01:04:47.548
<i>what with the anesthesia,</i>

01:04:47.581 --> 01:04:50.251
<i>I slept a great deal.</i>

01:04:50.284 --> 01:04:52.320
<i>I remember vaguely thinking</i>

01:04:52.353 --> 01:04:55.323
<i>I was married
to Olivia Hutton.</i>

01:04:55.356 --> 01:04:58.059
<i>I remember us
sharing a bedroom,</i>

01:04:58.092 --> 01:05:00.194
<i>of me going off to work,</i>

01:05:00.228 --> 01:05:02.697
<i>of an argument
we had over dinner,</i>

01:05:02.731 --> 01:05:05.701
<i>of a long drive through
a series of small towns,</i>

01:05:05.733 --> 01:05:08.670
<i>and then us
reaching the ocean,</i>

01:05:08.704 --> 01:05:11.472
<i>and a cabin by the ocean.</i>

01:05:11.505 --> 01:05:14.042
<i>It's strange, being dead,</i>

01:05:14.076 --> 01:05:17.146
<i>as I am now and have been
for I don't know how long,</i>

01:05:17.179 --> 01:05:21.150
<i>if "now" can be said
to mean anything any longer,</i>

01:05:21.182 --> 01:05:24.353
<i>that I remember those dreams
as accurately</i>

01:05:24.385 --> 01:05:27.923
<i>as anything I actually
experienced in reality.</i>

01:05:31.059 --> 01:05:32.961
Good morning.

01:05:35.063 --> 01:05:36.432
You're in
the hospital, son.

01:05:36.465 --> 01:05:38.534
<i>You had your appendix
removed.</i>

01:05:38.567 --> 01:05:41.235
<i>Just in the nick of time,
the doctors say.</i>

01:05:41.268 --> 01:05:43.371
I had my what?

01:05:43.405 --> 01:05:45.374
<i>Your appendix out.</i>

01:05:45.407 --> 01:05:47.209
Your dean
from the college,

01:05:47.242 --> 01:05:48.711
Mr. Caudwell,
was just now here.

01:05:48.744 --> 01:05:51.380
I sent him home,
didn't want to wake you.

01:05:51.413 --> 01:05:52.447
He's called
your parents.

01:05:52.481 --> 01:05:54.283
They know
you're fine.

01:05:54.315 --> 01:05:57.218
Your mother will be
here in a few days,

01:05:57.251 --> 01:05:58.753
and you're to call
your father.

01:05:58.786 --> 01:06:00.989
But first...

01:06:01.023 --> 01:06:04.026
I need you
to do some business for me into this.

01:06:15.570 --> 01:06:17.405
It's no fun being
in the hospital alone.

01:06:17.438 --> 01:06:19.741
Brought these over
to keep you company.

01:06:19.775 --> 01:06:21.744
It was worth
the appendicitis.

01:06:21.777 --> 01:06:23.579
I doubt it.

01:06:25.514 --> 01:06:27.416
Were you in
a lot of pain?

01:06:27.449 --> 01:06:32.153
For about an hour or so
before I blacked out.

01:06:32.186 --> 01:06:34.389
Best part came
in Dean Caudwell's office.

01:06:34.422 --> 01:06:37.625
<i>He called me in to grill me about
changing my dorm.</i>

01:06:37.659 --> 01:06:40.596
<i>I puked all over his trophies.
Then you turn up.</i>

01:06:40.628 --> 01:06:44.065
It's been a great case
of appendicitis all around.

01:06:44.099 --> 01:06:46.702
Let me get something
to put these in.

01:06:52.541 --> 01:06:55.344
Where will you be able
to see these best?

01:06:55.376 --> 01:06:58.112
<i>I see them best
in your two hands.</i>

01:06:58.146 --> 01:07:01.784
I see them best
with you standing right there.

01:07:01.817 --> 01:07:04.786
Just stay like that
for the next couple of days.

01:07:04.820 --> 01:07:07.189
What are they
giving you to eat?

01:07:07.222 --> 01:07:09.191
Jell-O, ginger ale.

01:07:09.224 --> 01:07:11.559
Tomorrow I start
on the snails.

01:07:11.592 --> 01:07:13.594
You seem very chipper.

01:07:13.628 --> 01:07:15.231
I am.

01:07:19.634 --> 01:07:21.202
Can I see?

01:07:21.235 --> 01:07:23.438
My stitches?

01:07:28.844 --> 01:07:30.046
Okay.

01:07:35.884 --> 01:07:38.519
Is the wound draining?

01:07:38.552 --> 01:07:41.389
Is that tube
dangling down there a drain?

01:07:42.690 --> 01:07:45.427
I don't know.
I suppose so. Yeah.

01:07:47.596 --> 01:07:49.831
What about the stitches?

01:07:52.666 --> 01:07:55.269
Well,
we're in a hospital.

01:07:55.302 --> 01:07:58.272
What better place
to be when they come undone?

01:07:58.306 --> 01:08:00.608
You're odd, you know?

01:08:02.210 --> 01:08:05.380
Odder than I think
you realize.

01:08:05.413 --> 01:08:08.317
I'm always odd after
I have my appendix taken out.

01:08:08.349 --> 01:08:10.318
Do you always
get as big as this

01:08:10.351 --> 01:08:13.321
after you have
your appendix out?

01:08:13.355 --> 01:08:16.323
It never fails.

01:08:16.358 --> 01:08:18.527
Mm.

01:08:18.560 --> 01:08:20.429
Of course, we shouldn't.

01:08:20.462 --> 01:08:22.831
We could both get thrown out
of school for this.

01:08:22.863 --> 01:08:25.100
Then stop.

01:08:36.944 --> 01:08:39.180
"I shot an arrow
into the air.

01:08:39.212 --> 01:08:40.747
It fell to earth
I knew not where."

01:08:44.350 --> 01:08:46.188
Excuse me.

01:08:46.220 --> 01:08:49.323
Oh. Oh, my God.

01:08:49.356 --> 01:08:50.559
<i>W... What is she
going to do now?</i>

01:08:50.591 --> 01:08:52.661
Nothing.

01:08:52.694 --> 01:08:54.496
<i>What do you mean, nothing?
I mean, how can you be so...</i>

01:08:54.529 --> 01:08:56.798
poised about all this?

01:08:56.831 --> 01:08:58.734
I mean, one call to the dean,
and we're out.

01:08:58.765 --> 01:09:00.536
How do you know she's
going to do nothing?

01:09:00.569 --> 01:09:03.538
She's too embarrassed to.

01:09:03.572 --> 01:09:06.375
<i>I don't... I don't understand
how you could be so...</i>

01:09:06.408 --> 01:09:07.776
So what?

01:09:07.809 --> 01:09:09.377
<i>Uh...</i>

01:09:09.411 --> 01:09:11.779
Under control.
So expert.

01:09:11.813 --> 01:09:13.747
<i>Oh, yes,</i>

01:09:13.782 --> 01:09:16.185
<i>Olivia the expert.</i>

01:09:16.216 --> 01:09:18.519
<i>That's what they called me
at the Menninger Clinic.</i>

01:09:18.551 --> 01:09:19.921
But you are.

01:09:19.953 --> 01:09:22.423
You really think so,
do you?

01:09:24.292 --> 01:09:27.196
I, who have
8,000 moods a minute,

01:09:27.229 --> 01:09:29.398
whose every emotion
is a tornado,

01:09:29.430 --> 01:09:30.698
who can be thrown
by a word,

01:09:30.731 --> 01:09:33.502
by a syllable,
am under control?

01:09:35.770 --> 01:09:37.706
You are blind.

01:09:48.917 --> 01:09:50.553
Do you hate me?

01:09:51.920 --> 01:09:53.720
<i>No.</i>

01:09:53.755 --> 01:09:56.725
I don't hate you.

01:09:56.757 --> 01:09:59.260
I think
maybe you hate me.

01:09:59.293 --> 01:10:01.529
Maybe you should.

01:10:12.539 --> 01:10:14.210
Will you come tomorrow?

01:10:17.945 --> 01:10:20.381
Yes.

01:10:46.975 --> 01:10:50.012
I need to see you walk to the end
of the hall and back with this.

01:10:50.045 --> 01:10:52.847
Then you can use
