Oh, Markie,
darling.

01:23:20.828 --> 01:23:22.397
Should I?

01:23:22.430 --> 01:23:24.365
Can I possibly?

01:23:25.733 --> 01:23:29.103
I came all this way
to ask you.

01:23:29.136 --> 01:23:31.306
You're the only one
I can ask about this.

01:23:33.073 --> 01:23:35.643
Could you possibly what?

01:23:35.676 --> 01:23:37.178
What?

01:23:37.211 --> 01:23:38.579
I can't say the word.

01:23:38.612 --> 01:23:40.215
What word?

01:23:42.149 --> 01:23:43.785
Divorce.

01:23:45.453 --> 01:23:46.454
Oh, Ma.

01:23:46.487 --> 01:23:48.588
Ma, you're
in a state of shock.

01:23:48.622 --> 01:23:50.758
You don't know what
you're saying. This...

01:23:50.791 --> 01:23:53.494
you've been married
to him for 25 years.

01:23:53.527 --> 01:23:55.363
- You love him.
- I don't.

01:23:56.863 --> 01:23:59.299
I hate him.

01:23:59.332 --> 01:24:03.203
I sit in the car as he's driving
and screaming at me,

01:24:03.237 --> 01:24:04.838
and I hate him
and loathe him

01:24:04.872 --> 01:24:06.474
from the bottom
of my heart.

01:24:06.506 --> 01:24:08.175
<i>I, It isn't true.</i>

01:24:08.208 --> 01:24:09.577
Even if it seems so,

01:24:09.609 --> 01:24:11.545
it's not
a permanent condition.

01:24:11.578 --> 01:24:16.550
Just see
Dr. Shildkret, please,

01:24:16.583 --> 01:24:19.086
at least as a start.

01:24:19.119 --> 01:24:20.521
Do it for me.

01:24:21.822 --> 01:24:23.623
I'm seeing a lawyer.

01:24:23.657 --> 01:24:24.759
What?!

01:24:24.792 --> 01:24:25.793
<i>Yes.</i>

01:24:25.826 --> 01:24:27.395
I've already seen him.

01:24:28.863 --> 01:24:31.332
I have an attorney.

01:24:51.351 --> 01:24:54.255
So you met in American,
you said?

01:24:54.287 --> 01:24:57.157
American History
to 1865.

01:24:57.190 --> 01:25:00.795
I'm also taking Principles
of American Government,

01:25:00.828 --> 01:25:02.830
but Olivia is just
in American History.

01:25:02.863 --> 01:25:05.833
That's why she brought
the textbook, Mom, so I can study.

01:25:05.865 --> 01:25:09.737
Your son, Mrs. Messner,
is a star student.

01:25:09.770 --> 01:25:13.474
He always asks the most interesting
questions in class.

01:25:13.506 --> 01:25:16.911
I wouldn't be surprised
if Professor Sundquist

01:25:16.944 --> 01:25:19.580
<i>weren't a bit intimidated
by Marcus.</i>

01:25:19.613 --> 01:25:22.350
Marcus has always been
a straight-A student.

01:25:22.382 --> 01:25:24.551
It's because of that
he has been awarded the scholarship.

01:25:24.585 --> 01:25:25.819
And you,

01:25:25.853 --> 01:25:28.155
Miss Hutton,
do you...

01:25:28.189 --> 01:25:30.859
are you enjoying
your studies?

01:25:33.327 --> 01:25:36.297
I enjoy the books, yes.

01:25:36.329 --> 01:25:38.599
I'm going to be
a French Literature major.

01:25:38.631 --> 01:25:40.701
French literature.

01:25:40.734 --> 01:25:43.304
Is this something of which your
parents approve?

01:25:43.337 --> 01:25:47.307
Well, my father is
a very practical man,

01:25:47.341 --> 01:25:49.810
but he hasn't suggested
any alternative,

01:25:49.842 --> 01:25:51.412
so I have to assume
that he believes,

01:25:51.444 --> 01:25:52.913
from a practical
perspective,

01:25:52.947 --> 01:25:55.550
that it would be a waste of his time
to think about it.

01:25:55.582 --> 01:25:58.418
And your mother,
Miss Hutton?

01:25:58.452 --> 01:26:01.588
<i>Well, my mother isn't
very practical at all,</i>

01:26:01.622 --> 01:26:04.192
but she has visited Paris
and loved it,

01:26:04.225 --> 01:26:07.528
so I think I should have her
vote if it should come to it.

01:26:07.560 --> 01:26:10.463
Sounds like you have
a very democratic household.

01:26:10.497 --> 01:26:12.233
That's very American.

01:26:13.600 --> 01:26:16.570
Yes, we are, American.

01:26:16.604 --> 01:26:19.907
Though as a student of American
civilization, Marcus,

01:26:19.939 --> 01:26:22.909
you must remember how Benjamin
Franklin once defined democracy.

01:26:22.943 --> 01:26:25.378
"Democracy," he said,

01:26:25.412 --> 01:26:28.416
"is two wolves and a lamb voting
on what to have for lunch."

01:28:17.390 --> 01:28:18.725
Ma.

01:28:18.759 --> 01:28:21.628
Marcus, I won't
divorce him.

01:28:24.131 --> 01:28:26.067
I'll bear him.

01:28:26.100 --> 01:28:28.303
I'll do all I can
to help him.

01:28:29.903 --> 01:28:33.440
I'm sorry I even allowed myself
to have such thoughts.

01:28:33.474 --> 01:28:36.110
I'm sorry
I told them to you.

01:28:36.143 --> 01:28:38.712
The way that I did it,
here at this hospital,

01:28:38.746 --> 01:28:41.716
with you just out of bed and
starting to walk around on your own,

01:28:41.748 --> 01:28:44.719
that wasn't right.
I apologize.

01:28:44.752 --> 01:28:47.689
I wasn't
thinking of you.

01:28:49.155 --> 01:28:52.126
Marcus,
you appear so strong,

01:28:52.158 --> 01:28:54.627
you are
in so many ways,

01:28:54.661 --> 01:28:58.065
that I forget you are a boy,
a very sensitive boy...

01:28:59.466 --> 01:29:02.070
a boy who loves
and honors his father.

01:29:05.405 --> 01:29:06.774
Yeah,
you can cry, Markie.

01:29:06.806 --> 01:29:09.010
- Ah, Ma.
- I've seen you cry before.

01:29:10.778 --> 01:29:13.447
I know.
I know I can. I know.

01:29:13.479 --> 01:29:16.116
I just don't want to.

01:29:19.853 --> 01:29:22.556
Thank you.

01:29:22.588 --> 01:29:23.791
Thank you, Ma.

01:29:23.823 --> 01:29:26.426
This is a great
relief to me.

01:29:27.994 --> 01:29:30.898
I couldn't imagine him
living all alone.

01:29:30.930 --> 01:29:32.500
It was unimaginable.

01:29:32.533 --> 01:29:34.469
Don't imagine it.

01:29:39.105 --> 01:29:42.510
But now I must ask
for something in return,

01:29:42.542 --> 01:29:45.512
because something
is unimaginable to me.

01:29:48.181 --> 01:29:50.917
I never asked
anything of you before.

01:29:50.951 --> 01:29:52.720
I never asked,
because I never had to,

01:29:52.752 --> 01:29:55.188
because you are perfect
where sons are concerned.

01:29:55.221 --> 01:29:58.858
All you've ever wanted
to be is a boy who does well.

01:29:58.891 --> 01:30:01.729
You have been the best son
a mother could have.

01:30:01.761 --> 01:30:03.163
But I am
going to ask you

01:30:03.197 --> 01:30:06.434
to have nothing more
to do with Miss Hutton...

01:30:06.466 --> 01:30:09.737
because for you to be with her
is unimaginable for me.

01:30:10.970 --> 01:30:12.105
Ma...

01:30:12.139 --> 01:30:14.074
Markie, you are here
to be a student

01:30:14.106 --> 01:30:15.975
and to study
the Supreme Court

01:30:16.009 --> 01:30:17.978
and to prepare
to go to law school.

01:30:18.011 --> 01:30:20.714
You are here so someday you will
become a person in the community

01:30:20.747 --> 01:30:24.552
that other people look up to
and that they come to for help.

01:30:24.585 --> 01:30:27.121
You are here so you don't
have to be a Messner

01:30:27.154 --> 01:30:29.723
and work in a butcher shop
for the rest of your life.

01:30:29.756 --> 01:30:31.926
You are not here
to look for trouble

01:30:31.958 --> 01:30:34.194
with a girl who has taken
a razor and slit her wrists.

01:30:34.228 --> 01:30:36.197
Wrist.
She slit one wrist.

01:30:36.229 --> 01:30:38.998
One is enough.

01:30:39.032 --> 01:30:43.002
We have only two,
and one is too much.

01:30:43.036 --> 01:30:44.704
Ma, you don't understand.

01:30:44.738 --> 01:30:46.106
You think
I don't understand?

01:30:46.139 --> 01:30:48.476
You don't.
You don't understand.

01:30:48.509 --> 01:30:49.877
Markie, I will stay
with your father,

01:30:49.909 --> 01:30:52.579
but for this,
I am offering a deal.

01:30:52.613 --> 01:30:55.149
Markie, the world
is full of young women

01:30:55.181 --> 01:30:57.016
who have
not slit any wrists,

01:30:57.050 --> 01:30:58.619
who have slit nothing.

01:30:58.652 --> 01:31:00.253
They exist
by the millions.

01:31:00.287 --> 01:31:01.655
Find one of them.

01:31:01.688 --> 01:31:03.757
<i>She can be
a Gentile.</i>

01:31:03.789 --> 01:31:05.059
<i>She can
be anything.</i>

01:31:05.091 --> 01:31:06.893
<i>This is 1951.</i>

01:31:06.926 --> 01:31:09.095
<i>You don't live in the Old World.
Why should you?</i>

01:31:09.128 --> 01:31:11.599
Date anyone you want,
marry anyone you want,

01:31:11.631 --> 01:31:13.533
do whatever you want
with whoever you choose,

01:31:13.567 --> 01:31:15.869
as long as she's never
put a razor to herself.

01:31:15.903 --> 01:31:19.173
<i>A girl so wounded
as to do such a thing</i>

01:31:19.206 --> 01:31:20.673
<i>will wipe out
everything</i>

01:31:20.707 --> 01:31:23.143
<i>before your life
has even begun.</i>

01:31:23.176 --> 01:31:25.846
Ma, you don't understand.

01:31:25.878 --> 01:31:28.114
It's not as serious
a relationship as you think.

01:31:28.148 --> 01:31:30.284
Serious?
She is serious for you,

01:31:30.317 --> 01:31:33.287
because she is suffering,
she is weak.

01:31:33.319 --> 01:31:36.023
And weak people,
Markie, weak people are not harmless.

01:31:36.055 --> 01:31:38.024
Their weakness
is their strength.

01:31:38.057 --> 01:31:41.895
<i>A person so unstable
is a menace to you, Markie.</i>

01:31:41.929 --> 01:31:44.097
<i>And she is a beautiful
young woman.</i>

01:31:44.131 --> 01:31:46.534
<i>She looks
like a goddess.</i>

01:31:46.567 --> 01:31:48.903
Obviously she's
well brought up.

01:31:50.170 --> 01:31:52.239
Though maybe there is
more to her upbringing

01:31:52.271 --> 01:31:53.841
than meets the eye.

01:31:53.873 --> 01:31:55.608
You never know
about those things,

01:31:55.641 --> 01:31:58.144
about what goes on
in people's houses.

01:31:58.177 --> 01:32:00.113
When the child
goes wrong,

01:32:00.146 --> 01:32:01.748
look to the family.

01:32:03.082 --> 01:32:07.020
<i>Regardless, my heart
goes out to her.</i>

01:32:07.054 --> 01:32:08.622
<i>I pray for her.</i>

01:32:08.654 --> 01:32:11.057
<i>I have nothing
against her.</i>

01:32:11.091 --> 01:32:14.128
But you,
you are my son...

01:32:15.862 --> 01:32:18.065
and my only child...

01:32:19.231 --> 01:32:21.335
and I am your mother,

01:32:21.368 --> 01:32:24.772
who will, who must
do anything for you.

01:32:24.805 --> 01:32:26.606
<i>Do you understand?</i>

01:32:33.980 --> 01:32:35.949
I understand.

01:32:37.050 --> 01:32:38.619
I understand.

01:32:38.652 --> 01:32:40.921
And that means
you will promise,

01:32:40.953 --> 01:32:43.590
no matter the tears,
the pleas from her, no matter...

01:32:44.992 --> 01:32:48.229
you promise
this will end now.

01:32:58.971 --> 01:33:01.007
You promise?

01:33:02.208 --> 01:33:04.144
I promise.

01:33:06.279 --> 01:33:08.149
I promise.

01:33:12.185 --> 01:33:14.254
<i>...by late 1747,</i>

01:33:14.287 --> 01:33:16.957
<i>Celeron was marching
with over 200 French troops</i>

01:33:16.989 --> 01:33:19.626
<i>and a party of Indians
down through Pennsylvania</i>

01:33:19.659 --> 01:33:22.630
<i>and then southwest
over here to the Ohio country,</i>

01:33:22.662 --> 01:33:26.032
<i>reaching Pickawillany, where
the Ohio and Miami rivers meet</i>

01:33:26.065 --> 01:33:28.268
<i>and where Celeron engaged</i>

01:33:28.301 --> 01:33:31.038
<i>with the Miami Indian chief
known as Old Briton,</i>

01:33:31.070 --> 01:33:32.840
<i>who he threatened</i>

01:33:32.872 --> 01:33:35.842
<i>for continuing to betray him
with the British.</i>

01:33:40.413 --> 01:33:42.349
We have a wonderful
weekend planned.

01:33:42.381 --> 01:33:44.117
Going to Kenyon
with some brothers.

01:33:44.150 --> 01:33:46.252
That prick Harding just sprang
another another paper on us.

01:33:46.286 --> 01:33:47.855
There goes
my weekend.

01:33:47.887 --> 01:33:49.789
Harding? What are you
complaining about?

01:33:49.823 --> 01:33:51.158
He's the easiest grader
at Winesburg.

01:33:51.190 --> 01:33:52.425
<i>What class?
For World Empires?</i>

01:33:52.458 --> 01:33:54.728
<i>- Yeah.
- Had it last year.</i>

01:33:54.761 --> 01:33:57.297
<i>Honestly, just copy
off the Britannica entry,</i>

01:33:57.329 --> 01:34:00.300
<i>and he never sees it.
"B," guaranteed.</i>

01:34:00.332 --> 01:34:01.734
<i>Better yet,
just copy my paper.</i>

01:34:01.768 --> 01:34:03.770
<i>I have it
upstairs somewhere.</i>

01:34:03.804 --> 01:34:05.439
<i>That'd be great.
You know, I still owe you</i>

01:34:05.471 --> 01:34:07.106
<i>for that Nestrick paper
from last year.</i>

01:34:07.140 --> 01:34:09.076
<i>No problem. Anytime.</i>

01:34:09.109 --> 01:34:12.012
Sonny says you're in the market
for a proxy at Chapel.

01:34:12.045 --> 01:34:14.782
I got it all out of the way by
the end of sophomore year,

01:34:14.814 --> 01:34:17.216
and I just polished off
Kessler's last three,

01:34:17.250 --> 01:34:19.286
so I'm a free agent.

01:34:19.319 --> 01:34:21.288
<i>Sonny says you're
on scholarship.</i>

01:34:21.320 --> 01:34:24.225
<i>I'll cut my fee
to a buck and a half. Deal?</i>

01:34:25.492 --> 01:34:27.161
Sure.

01:34:29.362 --> 01:34:34.467
By definition,
the slope is given by "M",

01:34:34.501 --> 01:34:36.804
<i>which is
the change in "Y"</i>

01:34:36.837 --> 01:34:38.205
<i>over the change
in "X,"</i>

01:34:38.238 --> 01:34:43.844
<i>or delta "Y"
by delta "X."</i>

01:35:07.768 --> 01:35:10.971
Yes, I'm trying to reach
Miss Olivia Hutton.

01:35:11.003 --> 01:35:12.238
Is she there?

01:35:13.873 --> 01:35:16.109
Uh-huh.

01:35:16.143 --> 01:35:18.945
Yes, that's me.
I left word yesterday.

01:35:20.113 --> 01:35:21.481
I know.

01:35:23.850 --> 01:35:25.419
What was that?

01:35:25.452 --> 01:35:27.887
<i>Olivia Hutton
is no longer here.</i>

01:35:27.921 --> 01:35:29.155
<i>She's gone home.</i>

01:35:29.189 --> 01:35:31.525
Home? You mean
she's visiting home?

01:35:31.557 --> 01:35:34.528
<i>She's gone.
There's no reason to be calling here.</i>

01:35:53.479 --> 01:35:56.115
Is Dean Caudwell free,
if he has a minute?

01:35:56.149 --> 01:35:57.918
Why don't
you have a seat

01:35:57.951 --> 01:36:00.287
and we'll find out
if he can see you.

01:36:20.140 --> 01:36:23.110
Dean Caudwell,
Marcus Messner is here.

01:36:23.143 --> 01:36:24.944
<i>Caudwell:
Bring him in.</i>

01:36:37.556 --> 01:36:38.925
You look well,
Marcus.

01:36:38.958 --> 01:36:40.993
Maybe lost
a pound or two,

01:36:41.027 --> 01:36:42.529
but otherwise
you look fine.

01:36:44.130 --> 01:36:46.365
Dean Caudwell...

01:36:46.399 --> 01:36:48.468
I don't know
who else to turn to

01:36:48.501 --> 01:36:52.372
about something that is
very important to me.

01:36:52.404 --> 01:36:54.173
I didn't mean to throw up here,
you know.

01:36:54.207 --> 01:36:56.944
You fell ill,
and you were sick,

01:36:56.976 --> 01:36:58.612
and that's that.

01:36:58.645 --> 01:37:02.349
Lucky we got you
to the hospital in time.

01:37:02.381 --> 01:37:04.417
What can I do for you?

01:37:07.654 --> 01:37:10.958
I'm here about
a female student.

01:37:10.990 --> 01:37:13.359
She was
in my history class,

01:37:13.393 --> 01:37:16.363
and now she is gone.

01:37:16.395 --> 01:37:17.997
I told you
I'd been on one date.

01:37:18.030 --> 01:37:19.399
It had been with her.

01:37:19.431 --> 01:37:22.402
Her name
is Olivia Hutton.

01:37:22.435 --> 01:37:25.239
Now she has disappeared.

01:37:25.271 --> 01:37:27.306
I would like to know
what happened to her.

01:37:27.340 --> 01:37:29.009
I'm afraid something
terrible happened,

01:37:29.042 --> 01:37:32.613
and I'm afraid I may have
had something to do with it.

01:37:32.645 --> 01:37:35.014
What is it
you think you did

01:37:35.047 --> 01:37:36.449
that makes
you think this?

01:37:40.020 --> 01:37:41.588
I took her out
on a date.

01:37:41.621 --> 01:37:44.123
Did something
happen on that date

01:37:44.157 --> 01:37:45.993
you want
to tell me about?

01:37:47.027 --> 01:37:48.295
No, sir.

01:37:49.529 --> 01:37:51.398
Dean.

01:37:51.430 --> 01:37:54.300
I'm "Dean"
to you, please.

01:37:54.333 --> 01:37:58.137
The answer is no,
Dean Caudwell.

01:37:58.171 --> 01:38:00.474
Nothing happened that I would like
to tell you about.

01:38:03.243 --> 01:38:05.545
Did you impregnate
this young lady, Marcus?

01:38:05.578 --> 01:38:08.048
No... what?! No!

01:38:08.081 --> 01:38:09.483
You're sure?

01:38:09.515 --> 01:38:11.284
Absolutely sure.

01:38:11.318 --> 01:38:13.552
She wasn't pregnant,
as far as you know?

01:38:13.586 --> 01:38:15.155
No.

01:38:15.188 --> 01:38:18.292
You didn't force yourself
on Olivia Hutton?

01:38:18.324 --> 01:38:21.161
No, sir. I did not
force myself on her.

01:38:23.329 --> 01:38:26.300
She came and visited you
in your hospital room, did she not?

01:38:26.332 --> 01:38:28.301
Uh...

01:38:28.335 --> 01:38:30.604
Yes.
Yes, she did, Dean.

01:38:30.636 --> 01:38:33.172
According to a member
of the hospital staff,

01:38:33.206 --> 01:38:36.176
something occurred between
the two of you at the hospital.

01:38:36.208 --> 01:38:38.644
Something sordid
occurred

01:38:38.677 --> 01:38:41.213
that was observed
and duly noted.

01:38:41.247 --> 01:38:44.017
Yet you say you didn't
force yourself on her.

01:38:44.050 --> 01:38:45.686
I had just had
my appendix taken out.

01:38:45.719 --> 01:38:48.587
That doesn't answer
my question.

01:38:48.621 --> 01:38:51.057
No, sir, I did not.

01:38:51.091 --> 01:38:54.061
I've never used force
on anyone in my life.

01:38:54.094 --> 01:38:55.962
I've never had to.

01:38:55.996 --> 01:38:57.663
You didn't have to.

01:38:57.697 --> 01:38:59.699
May I ask
what that means?

01:38:59.733 --> 01:39:01.702
No. No, you can't.

01:39:03.502 --> 01:39:06.273
Dean Caudwell, this is very hard
for me to talk about,

01:39:06.305 --> 01:39:07.707
but I do think
that whatever happened

01:39:07.740 --> 01:39:10.243
in the privacy
of my hospital room

01:39:10.275 --> 01:39:12.045
was strictly
between Olivia and myself.

01:39:12.078 --> 01:39:14.982
Perhaps,
and perhaps not,

01:39:15.015 --> 01:39:18.252
especially in light
of the circumstances.

01:39:19.418 --> 01:39:20.386
Why?

01:39:20.420 --> 01:39:22.689
Olivia Hutton

01:39:22.721 --> 01:39:25.692
had a nervous
breakdown, Marcus.

01:39:25.725 --> 01:39:28.729
She had to be taken away
in an ambulance.

01:39:37.670 --> 01:39:39.306
I really don't know

01:39:39.338 --> 01:39:42.009
what goes into
a nervous breakdown.

01:39:43.409 --> 01:39:47.247
You lose control
over yourself and your emotions,

01:39:47.279 --> 01:39:50.016
like an infant.

01:39:50.050 --> 01:39:53.253
You have to be
hospitalized and cared for

01:39:53.286 --> 01:39:57.256
like an infant
until you recover,

01:39:57.289 --> 01:40:00.460
if you ever do recover.

01:40:00.493 --> 01:40:03.263
The college took a chance
with Olivia Hutton.

01:40:03.296 --> 01:40:05.532
We knew
her mental history,

01:40:05.564 --> 01:40:08.434
the relapses,
electroshock treatments,

01:40:08.467 --> 01:40:11.037
but her father
is a Cleveland surgeon

01:40:11.070 --> 01:40:14.041
and a distinguished
alumnus at Winesburg,

01:40:14.073 --> 01:40:17.810
and so we took her in
at Dr. Hutton's request.

01:40:17.844 --> 01:40:21.681
Things didn't work out
very well for any of us.

01:40:21.713 --> 01:40:24.417
They especially
didn't work out for Olivia.

01:40:25.685 --> 01:40:27.254
She is where?

01:40:27.287 --> 01:40:30.356
At a hospital specializing
in psychiatric care.

01:40:30.390 --> 01:40:34.194
She can't possibly
be pregnant, too.

01:40:34.226 --> 01:40:35.728
Time will tell.

01:40:39.599 --> 01:40:43.503
It's not me.

01:40:43.536 --> 01:40:47.707
What was reported to us about
your conduct at the hospital

01:40:47.739 --> 01:40:49.509
suggests it could be,
Marcus.

01:40:49.542 --> 01:40:52.312
I don't care
what it suggests.

01:40:52.345 --> 01:40:56.182
Dean Caudwell,
I will not be condemned

01:40:56.216 --> 01:40:59.352
on the basis
of no evidence.

01:40:59.385 --> 01:41:04.190
Sir, I resent, once again,

01:41:04.224 --> 01:41:06.126
your portrayal of me.

01:41:06.158 --> 01:41:09.795
I did not have sexual intercourse
with Olivia Hutton.

01:41:09.828 --> 01:41:13.099
I have never had sexual intercourse
with anyone.

01:41:13.132 --> 01:41:15.335
Nobody in this world

01:41:15.368 --> 01:41:17.604
could possibly be pregnant
because of me.

01:41:17.636 --> 01:41:19.605
It is impossible.

01:41:19.639 --> 01:41:21.274
Marcus,
it is possible.

01:41:21.306 --> 01:41:23.176
Ah, fuck you, it is.

